    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">January</hi> 22, 1894.—Referred to the
                            Committee on Foreign Affairs and ordered to be printed.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">The Congress:</hi>]</p>
                <p>I transmit herewith copies of dispatches received from our minister to
                            Hawaii after the arrival of those, copies of which accompanied my
                            message of the 20th instant.</p>
                <p>I also inclose for the information of the Congress copies of reports and
                            a copy of an order just received by the Secretary of the Navy from
                            Rear-Admiral Irwin, commanding our naval forces at Honolulu.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grover Cleveland.</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Executive
                                    Mansion</hi>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
